name: heat and power co-generation unit construction, organic Rankine cycle, 200kW electrical | heat and power co-generation unit, organic Rankine cycle, 200kW electrical | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3752/documentation

This dataset represent the production and the disposal of an organic rankine cycle unit. It is dimensioned to be connected to a biomass burning boiler (with capacity 1000kWth), producing about 200 kWel. 

From reception of unit components at the factory gate

This activity ends with the disposal of the device in the end of its lifetime.The dataset includes the most important materials used for the fabrication of a cogeneration heat and power unit with organic rankine cycle (ORC) technology: steel, chromium steel, copper, electronic components, plastics, insulation, organic fluid. The dataset also includes energy required for the construction and the disposal of the device. The unit includes an electricity generator, a compressor, a condenser, tubes and pipes for thermal oil distribution within the cycle. The dataset doesnt include the basement in concrete for the installation and emission from manufacture.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Organic rankine cycle unit of modern technology (2011). Data are taken from producers and technical information available. Model choosen: brand Turboden, Pratt&Whitney Power System Company, CHP Split (devices which are sold worldwide). This module describes a specific ORC Generation Unit for the production of heat and electricity from biomass fuel, dimensioned to be connected to a furnace with about 1000 kWth capacity.;Source of image: http://www.turboden.eu/en/public/downloads/Scheda%20Biomassa%20CHP%20Split%20-%20ING.pdf
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: literature, technical data available, personal communications from technicians and specialized producer company
